#: template-meaning-of-6.php:44
msgid "The Sixth Estate is what comes after the noise. It is journalism that is community-grounded rather than commercially captured. Language-first rather than language-last. Accountable to its readers rather than to its owners, its advertisers, or the government of the day. It does not wait for a press accreditation to tell the truth. It does not moderate its conclusions to preserve access to those in power."
