#: template-meaning-of-6.php:51
msgid "We are also aware that independent journalism in Malaysia operates under the shadow of laws designed less to protect the public than to protect power from scrutiny — among them Section 233 of the Communications and Multimedia Act 1998, known in practice, and with good reason, as the %s. We publish anyway. A law that exists to punish inconvenient expression is not a law that deserves our silence. It is a law that deserves to be named."
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:46
msgid "We are not neutral — neutrality is a convenient fiction used to avoid accountability. We are independent. We operate in Bahasa Melayu because that is where the conversation that matters to us lives, and because language is never merely a vehicle: it is a political choice. We answer to our readers. We are the Sixth Estate."
msgstr ""

#: template-editorial-policy.php:47
msgid "We believe that the responsibility of media is not merely to convey information, but to build public trust through responsible journalistic practice."
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:191
msgid "We did not build UP6 Suara Semasa to be comfortable. We built it to be useful. We built it to be honest. We built it to still be standing — and still publishing — when the pressure comes."
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:164
msgid "We do not accept the premise that a free press owes the state the benefit of the doubt. The state has lawyers, spokespersons, press secretaries and the full apparatus of official narrative. It does not need our help. The public, which has none of those things, does."
msgstr ""

#: template-privacy-policy.php:57
msgid "We do not collect identity card numbers, bank account details, or other sensitive information without your explicit consent."
msgstr ""

#: template-corrections.php:59
msgid "We do not issue corrections for matters of editorial judgement, word choice, or differences of opinion. If a report is disputed, we will consider the dispute on its merits and correct only where the record is demonstrably wrong."
msgstr ""

#: template-corrections.php:63
msgid "We do not scrub errors from the public record. The correction notice remains visible permanently alongside the corrected content, so that readers who encountered the original version are aware that it has been updated."
msgstr ""

#: template-privacy-policy.php:67
msgid "We do not use your information for direct marketing without your prior consent."
msgstr ""

#: template-editorial-policy.php:104
msgid "We exercise particular care when reporting on:"
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:146
msgid "We give the subjects of our reporting the right of reply. We present competing accounts where they exist and clearly label them as such. We distinguish between what is established and what is alleged. We do not use journalism as a weapon against individuals, and we do not use it as a shield for institutions. Fairness is a method, not a conclusion — and it is never an excuse for cowardice."
msgstr ""

#: template-disclaimer.php:60
msgid "We have no control over the nature, content, or availability of external websites. We accept no responsibility for any loss or inconvenience that may arise from your use of third-party content or websites reached through links on this portal."
msgstr ""

#: template-about.php:57
msgid "We hold ourselves to the standards set out in our Editorial Policy — accuracy, fairness, editorial independence and transparency in the use of sources. Corrections are published promptly and without reservation. Readers who identify errors are encouraged to write to us."
msgstr ""

#: template-privacy-policy.php:50
msgid "We may collect the following information when you interact with UP6 Suara Semasa:"
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:153
msgid "We name our sources where we can. Where we cannot, we explain why — not with a vague appeal to confidentiality, but with a specific account of the editorial judgement made. We do not hide our methods, our funding, our ownership or our limitations. Readers who disagree with our judgements are entitled to the information needed to challenge them."
msgstr ""

#: template-editorial-policy.php:115 template-editorial-policy.php:123
msgid "We recognise that a free press is not a courtesy extended by those in power — it is a right exercised in the public interest, regardless of whether that exercise is convenient for the powerful."
msgstr ""

#: template-privacy-policy.php:112
msgid "We retain your personal information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes stated in this policy, or as required by law. Anonymous analytics data is retained for a maximum period of 26 months."
msgstr ""

#: template-privacy-policy.php:90
msgid "We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorised access, loss, or disclosure. However, no data transmission over the internet can be guaranteed as fully secure."
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:202
msgid "We verify before we publish. Our word to the reader is the only currency we have, and we do not spend it carelessly."
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:132
msgid "We verify before we publish. We do not treat speed as an excuse for error, or traffic as a justification for speculation. Every claim that carries our name has been interrogated before it is printed — because our word to the reader is the only currency we have, and we do not spend it carelessly."
msgstr ""

#: template-contact.php:67
msgid "We welcome questions, tips, corrections, and feedback from readers, sources, and the public. The editorial team reads every message and will respond within three working days."
msgstr ""

#: template-meaning-of-6.php:163
msgid "We will name custodial deaths. We will report unlawful detention, the abuse of remand powers, and the use of force against civilians as the serious matters they are — not as isolated incidents, not as procedural anomalies, but as events that demand explanation from those responsible. We will not deploy the word alleged to protect institutions that have the full resources of the state at their disposal. We will not kill a story because someone in authority found it inconvenient."
msgstr ""

#: template-editorial-policy.php:114 template-editorial-policy.php:122
msgid "We will not reveal the identity of confidential sources under pressure from any authority. Journalists working under the UP6 name have the right to protect their sources, and UP6 will provide reasonable support to any journalist who faces legal or institutional pressure as a result of their work for this publication."
msgstr ""

#: index.php:63
